<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Zandar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-22 15:13:43</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>It can be found in Temple of Droga. A very nasty 35-45+ dungon. You have to drop in and once you do you are (dead) commited. If you do not have a good map,gate or an evac out Do not even go there. If you do not have a cleric, do not go there. If your 35 and have only a group of 35's? guess what? DO not go there! I was in a group last night all of us were 40+ and the entire group got squashed. But other then that i love the place, its exciting dangerous and well made. It has good loot, it is really fun but when you go make sure you dont mind dieing, because Noone hunts there . My group was 6 of the 6 players in this large dungon. Also Dont use pets at all the pathing is set so they train you and they do!. </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Alonnar</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-09 15:55:54</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Went there about a week ago and had 3 full groups of lvl 30-35 players. We got down to where the buildings were and started killing anything that came our way. Those goblins hit extremely hard! Spawn times are quick and we knew that we would soon be overran by the MOBs that we had killed earlier. We started back toward the entrance and found that the MOBs had respawned and brought friends. It seemed we were outnumbered 2 to 1. I think the rogue we had scouting did not know that he was pulling a train longer than the Mississippi River behind him. Out of the 18 people we had down there only part of my group made it out, and only due to the fact that 2 in our group gave their lives to make sure I got my evac off. Very dangerous. It is like a lvl 35+ Blackburrow.</font></td></tr></table>
